.TH "msc_buffer_win_alloc" 9 "msc_buffer_win_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
msc_buffer_win_alloc \- alloc a window for a multiblock mode
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" msc_buffer_win_alloc
.BI "(struct msc *msc "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nr_blocks "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "msc" 12
MSC device
.IP "nr_blocks" 12
number of pages in this window
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This modifies msc::win_list and msc::base, which requires msc::buf_mutex
to serialize, so the caller is expected to hold it.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno otherwise.
